  "text": "In AIME, the mentees were not acted upon but rather some practiced resistance in quite overt ways such as refusing to speak, listening to their IPods or not completing tasks. Mentors recognised these actions not as acts of deviance or defiance, but as acceptable actions on the part of young people finding personal place and space. This could be understood as an element of what [CITATION_1] describe as the desire to \"play\". In their UK study of working class students, in order to encourage young people to consider higher education, they not only require the:",
